verbs.description: underfeel (third-person singular simple present underfeels, present participle underfeeling, simple past and past participle underfelt)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To secretly gain knowledge from.
examples: Then having done, added farther, that he had endeavoured to underfeel the fellow that was below, but he found him very obstinate,  […]

entries.meaning: (transitive and intransitive) To feel inadequately or to a lesser degree than expected.
